</head>
<body>

<h1>Empathic Response Toolkit – Quick Reference</h1>

<h2>Supportive Language &amp; Goals</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Supportive Language</th><th>Goal / Reminder</th></tr>
  <tr><td>“Let’s pause for a second and feel the ground under you.”</td><td>Re‑orient; steady breathing.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>“It sounds unbearable. You don’t have to face this alone; we can find someone trained to help.”</td><td>Re‑establish connection and agency.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>“You matter; these feelings won’t last forever. I can listen and help you reach out for more support.”</td><td>Affirm worth and belonging.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>“It’s okay to feel angry; let’s slow it down so it doesn’t overwhelm you.”</td><td>Lower arousal; maintain safety.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>“Let’s take one thing at a time; what feels most important right now?”</td><td>Restore clarity and cognitive control.</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>Crisis Note:</strong> If anyone is in immediate danger or thinking of self‑harm, call local emergency services or one of these resources:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://988lifeline.org">988 Suicide &amp; Crisis Lifeline (US)</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://findahelpline.com">Find International Hotlines ↗︎</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>Boundaries &amp; Ethical Reminders</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>I’m not a therapist</strong> and do not provide clinical treatment.</li>
  <li>I can <strong>listen</strong>, share coping ideas, and help connect you with <strong>licensed professionals</strong>.</li>
  <li>Keep consent and comfort central — ask what feels helpful.</li>
  <li>Encourage multiple supports: trusted people, hotlines, and professional care.</li>
  <li><strong>Honesty + consistency + non‑judgment</strong> = real safety.</li>
  <li>If someone expresses suicidal thoughts or intent to harm, <strong>guide them immediately</strong> to emergency or crisis resources.</li>
</ul>

<footer>
  Optional space for local hotline numbers, organization logo, or QR links to additional resources.  
  <br><em>This toolkit offers peer‑support guidance only; it is not clinical or therapeutic advice.</em>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
```

Open this file in a browser and **print to PDF (landscape)** to get a crisp, one‑page reference; or keep it digital for phones/tablets.  
The visible disclaimer and hotline links stay on screen in every format.

